dicate that higher temperatures promote more pointed wings, which may provide energetic benefits. Our results show the importance of including both climatic and land-\u00aduse variables when assessing trends in bat morphology and exploring interactions. Encouragingly, all three species have shown an ability to adapt their body size and functional traits to different conditions, and it could demonstrate their potential to overcome future negative impacts of climate and land-\u00aduse change.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Wood, Heather", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cousins, Sara A. O.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/c77324844022c158435fc51aaeb7bd05", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/48892e9e15511b5ee639e9d276a6387d293bfc42618ec048305533d008bc00dd", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/AHJBRTZ8", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/AHJBRTZ8", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/3938642318353154b1e51d96ac6dbd40!/b22292-24765", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "e9695", "title": "Ecology and Evolution", "volume": "13"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/c77324844022c158435fc51aaeb7bd05"